C02: 3D Geometry	The waveform visualization must be generated using 3D rendering libraries (e.g., Three.js, OpenGL, or a custom engine) where the Y-axis represents amplitude and the X and Z axes define the physical space.	Minimum Vertices: ≥500 vertices per frame for smooth 3D curves. Waveform Type: Must support parametric curves for a "wave" appearance, not just static bars.
C03: Real-Time Sync	The animation framerate must be perfectly synchronized with the audio processing. Every video frame must correspond to an analyzed audio block to prevent visual stutter or drift.	Target Sync Rate: 1:1 match between video frames and audio analysis cycles. Tolerance: Animation lag must be virtually zero (≈0 ms).
C04: Input Audio	The system must accept and decode high-quality audio formats before processing.	Supported Formats: .WAV (uncompressed preferred), .FLAC, or high-bitrate .MP3/.AAC. Sample Rate: Must handle up to 48 kHz.

