II. Visual Quality & Effects Rules (3D/Shaders)
Rule ID	Rule Description	Constraint/Parameter
V01: Dynamic Shadows	The 3D waveform object must cast realistic, dynamic shadows onto the background plane. Shadows must change based on the virtual light source's position and the waveform's movement.	Shadow Technique: Use a performant technique like Variance Shadow Maps (VSM) or high-resolution Shadow Mapping (≥2048 resolution).
V02: Volumetric Lighting	Implement a volumetric or ambient occlusion effect to enhance the 3D depth and define the shape of the waveform with realistic lighting and soft glow.	Effect: Must include an Ambient Occlusion (AO) or Bloom filter on the waveform edges. Light Source: Must support customizable 3D light position and color.
V03: Reflection/Refraction	The waveform material must have customizable properties including reflectivity and material color/texture. Rule: A subtle ground reflection or self-reflection on the waveform surface is mandatory.	Shaders: PBR (Physically Based Rendering) pipeline recommended for materials. Surface: Must allow user control over Metallic and Roughness values.
V04: Post-Processing	Apply a final cinematic look before export.	Required Filters: Anti-aliasing (e.g., TAA, FXAA), Depth of Field (DOF) for customizable focus, and a slight Color Grade/Vignette.

