III. YouTube Optimization & Export Rules
Rule ID	Rule Description	Constraint/Parameter
Y01: Output Resolution	The final video must be exported to meet YouTube's high-definition standards.	Standard: 1920×1080 (1080p). Premium Option: 3840×2160 (4K UHD) as a maximum setting.
Y02: Output Framerate	The rendering engine must target and maintain a high, stable framerate for buttery-smooth animation, which YouTube highly rewards.	Target Framerate: 60 Frames Per Second (FPS). Minimum Acceptable: 30 FPS.
Y03: Encoding Parameters	Use YouTube's recommended encoding settings for maximum quality retention after re-encoding.	Codec: H.264. Container: MP4. Bitrate: User-selectable constant bitrate (CBR) or VBR with a high ceiling (e.g., ≥50 Mbps for 4K or ≥15 Mbps for 1080p).
Y04: Audio Encoding	Encode the audio in the final video using the highest possible quality.	Audio Codec: AAC-LC. Bitrate: ≥384 kbps. Sample Rate: 48 kHz.

